---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'March 1, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Matrix Digital Media"
  description="Privacy policy for all apps published by Matrix Digital Media LLC."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="policy-page">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="policy-header">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">← Home</a>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="meta">Matrix Digital Media LLC &mdash; Last updated {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-body">

        <p class="intro">
          This Privacy Policy applies to all mobile applications and digital products published
          by <strong>Matrix Digital Media LLC</strong> ("we," "us," or "our"), including HiveHelper
          and any future apps. By using our apps, you agree to the practices described below.
        </p>

        <section>
          <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

          <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
          <p>
            Our apps allow you to enter and store content such as inspection logs, notes,
            observations, and other data you create within the app. This information is entered
            voluntarily and is stored locally on your device. We do not access or read the
            content of your personal entries.
          </p>

          <h3>Photos</h3>
          <p>
            If you attach photos within our apps, those photos are stored locally on your device.
            They are not uploaded to our servers or shared with third parties unless explicitly
            stated within a specific feature.
          </p>

          <h3>Usage and Analytics Data</h3>
          <p>
            We collect anonymous usage data to understand how our apps are used and to improve
            the experience. This includes information such as which features are used, how often,
            and general interaction patterns. This data does not include the content of your
            personal entries and is not linked to your identity.
          </p>
          <p>
            Analytics are powered by <strong>Firebase Analytics</strong> (Google LLC). For more
            information on how Firebase handles data, visit
            <a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              firebase.google.com/support/privacy
            </a>.
          </p>

          <h3>Purchase Information</h3>
          <p>
            If you make an in-app purchase, the transaction is processed entirely by Apple through
            the App Store. We receive confirmation of your purchase status (e.g., active
            subscription) but do not receive your payment details, credit card information, or
            billing address.
          </p>

          <h3>Device Information</h3>
          <p>
            We may collect general device information such as operating system version and device
            type for the purpose of crash reporting and compatibility improvements.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>To provide and maintain app functionality</li>
            <li>To understand usage patterns and improve our products</li>
            <li>To verify purchase and subscription status</li>
            <li>To diagnose crashes and technical issues</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do not sell your information to third parties. We do not use your data for
            targeted advertising.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. Data Storage</h2>
          <p>
            By default, all personal data you enter into our apps is stored locally on your
            device using on-device storage. This data is not transmitted to our servers and
            is not accessible to us.
          </p>
          <p>
            In future versions of our apps, we may offer optional cloud backup or sync features
            powered by <strong>Firebase</strong> (Google LLC). If and when such features are
            introduced, they will be opt-in, clearly disclosed, and this policy will be updated
            accordingly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>Our apps may integrate with the following third-party services:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Apple App Store / StoreKit</strong> — for processing in-app purchases and
              subscriptions. Subject to
              <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apple's Privacy Policy</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Firebase Analytics (Google LLC)</strong> — for anonymous usage analytics.
              Subject to
              <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We may add additional third-party services in the future. This policy will be updated
            to reflect any such additions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. User Accounts</h2>
          <p>
            Our current apps do not require you to create an account or provide personally
            identifying information such as your name or email address to use core features.
            Future versions may offer optional account creation to enable features such as
            cloud sync across devices.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
          <p>
            All locally stored data remains on your device until you delete it within the app
            or uninstall the app. Uninstalling the app will remove all locally stored data
            associated with it. Anonymous analytics data is retained per Firebase's standard
            retention policies.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our apps are not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly
            collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has
            provided us with personal information, please contact us and we will take steps
            to delete it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>
            Because we do not collect personally identifiable information under normal app usage,
            there is typically no personal data held by us to access, correct, or delete. If you
            have concerns about data collected through analytics or future cloud features, you
            may contact us at any time.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the
            "Last updated" date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this policy
            periodically. Continued use of our apps after changes are posted constitutes
            acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:<br />
            <a href="mailto:hello@matrixnj.com">hello@matrixnj.com</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            Matrix Digital Media LLC<br />
            New Jersey, United States
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .policy-page {
    padding-top: calc(var(--header-h) + 4rem);
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .policy-header {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .back-link:hover { color: var(--text); }

  .policy-header h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .meta {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .policy-body {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem 1.25rem;
  }

  ul li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent-1);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  a:hover { opacity: 0.8; }

  strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
